data.enText: to force sb to have sex with you when they do not want to by threatening them or using violence
the crime of forcing sb to have sex with you, especially using violence

data.chText: 强奸案报案数字的增加
data.enText: an increase in the number of reported rapes

data.chText: 肆意损坏；肆意糟蹋；蹂躏
data.enText: the act of destroying or spoiling an area in a way that seems unnecessary
a plant with bright yellow flowers, grown as food for farm animals and for its seeds that are used to make oil

simple_means.memory_skill: rap 捕，夺 + e → 洗劫；强奸

tr: the crime of forcing a woman to submit to sexual intercourse against her will
the act of despoiling a country in warfare
Eurasian plant cultivated for its seed and as a forage crop
destroy and strip of its possession
example: The soldiers raped the beautiful country

tr: force (someone) to have sex against their will
example: The woman was raped on her way home at night

value.def: If someone is raped, they are forced to have sex, usually by violence or threats of violence.

example.ex: A young woman was brutally raped in her own home...
example.tran: 一名年轻女子在自己家中惨遭强暴。

value.def: Rape is the crime of forcing someone to have sex.

example.ex: Her party opposes abortion, except in cases of rape or incest...
example.tran: 她的党派反对堕胎，但强奸或乱伦引起的怀孕除外。

example.ex: Almost ninety per cent of all rapes and violent assaults went unreported.
example.tran: 几乎90%的强奸案和暴力侵害案都没有报案。

value.def: The rape of an area or of a country is the destruction or spoiling of it.

example.ex: As a result of the rape of the forests, parts of the country are now short of water.
example.tran: 由于森林遭到破坏，目前该国的部分地区水源短缺。

value.def: Rape is a plant with yellow flowers which is grown as a crop. Its seeds are crushed to make cooking oil.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 oilseed rape

trans: 法定强奸罪(与未成年少女发生性行为)

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to seize, to snatch 捕, 夺
rootsaffixes.title: rap(t), rav

partsOfSpeech.dec: en 使… + rapture 狂喜 → 使狂喜
rap 捕，夺 + acious 有…性质的 → 抢夺的
rap 捕，夺 + e → 洗劫；强奸
rap 捕，夺 + ine 表抽象名词 → 抢夺

partsOfSpeech.d: 着迷的（魂被夺走 → 着迷的）

partsOfSpeech.dec: rapt 捕，夺 + or 表动物 → 善于掠夺的动物 → 猛禽
rapt 捕，夺 + ure 表行为 → 捕获梦想 → 狂喜
rav 捕，夺 + age 表行为或行为的结果 → 你争我夺 → 破坏
rav 捕，夺 + en 使… → 捕获食物 → 捕食
raven 捕食；狼吞虎咽 + ous …的 → 不断捕食的 → 贪婪的；饿极的
rav 捕，夺 + ish 使… → 抢夺
